Privacy Policy

Last Updated: 8/11/2024

This Privacy Policy explains how Ego ("the Bot") collects, uses, and protects information obtained from users ("you") when you interact with the Bot.

1. Information We Collect
1.1. User Data

The Bot may collect certain information provided by you when interacting with the Bot, such as Discord user IDs, usernames, and messages.
The Bot may collect data related to your interactions with the Bot, including commands used and responses generated.
1.2. Server Data

The Bot may collect information about the Discord servers in which it is active, including server IDs, channel IDs, and server settings relevant to the Bot's functionality.
1.3. Technical Data

The Bot may collect technical data, such as your IP address, browser type, and operating system, through the Discord API or when interacting with the Bot's web services.
2. How We Use Your Information
2.1. Provide and Improve Services

The information collected is used to provide, maintain, and improve the Botâ€™s functionality. This includes responding to commands, processing interactions, and providing personalized experiences.
2.2. Analytics

The Bot may use collected data to analyze usage patterns and improve the Bot's performance and user experience.
2.3. Communication

The Bot may use your information to communicate with you regarding updates, support, and service-related announcements.
3. Data Sharing and Disclosure
3.1. Third-Party Services

The Bot may use third-party services to provide certain features or to process data. These services are governed by their own privacy policies.
3.2. Legal Requirements

We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or if such action is necessary to comply with legal obligations.
3.3. Business Transfers

In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred to the new owner or entity.
4. Data Security
4.1. Security Measures

We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of data transmission or storage is completely secure.
4.2. Retention

We retain your data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy or as required by law.
5. Your Choices
5.1. Opt-Out

You may choose to opt-out of certain data collection or request the deletion of your data by contacting us directly.
5.2. Data Access

You have the right to access, update, or request the deletion of the personal information we hold about you. To exercise these rights, please contact us at vhskyrie@pm.me.
6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the "Last Updated" date will be revised accordingly. Your continued use of the Bot after any changes signifies your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.

7. Contact Information
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

